data.description: Is the summer heat driving up your electric bill?? Demand for efficient-efficient homes is on the rise, and I happen to have one located right here in Gatesville. The owner of this property purchased and installed solar panels last year, nearly eliminating the monthly electric bill (July 2023 electric bill was only $53!!). These solar panels were nearly a $50K investment by seller that buyer would get for FREE!!  Another awesome feature of this property is that it backs up to the Gatesville Country Club (the 5th fairway is on the other side of the back yard fence). The home was built in 2013, has 3 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, and contains approx. 1600 sq. ft. of living space. Other features include a separate floor plan with private master bedroom and bathroom with his and her walk-in closets, double vanity in both bathrooms, all electric, granite counter, tile backsplash and custom cabinets in kitchen, breakfast bar separating dining room from kitchen, sprinkler system, wood privacy fenced yard, and two car garage. As previously mentioned, the home sits on nearly quarter acre sized lot adjacent to the golf course - a very short golf cart ride to the club house. Come take a look at this wonderful property before it's gone!!
